        "heading": "Lever 1: Model Right-Sizing",
        "content": "The biggest single savings. Most tasks don't need Opus.\n\n### Decision Tree\n```\nIs the task mechanical / deterministic?\n  YES → Haiku ($1/$5)\n    • Classification, extraction, formatting, routing, tagging\n    • Simple Q&A from provided context\n    \n  NO → Does it require multi-step reasoning?\n    NO → Sonnet ($3/$15)\n      • Code generation, summarization, analysis\n      • Structured output, content creation\n      • Code review, test writing\n      \n    YES → Is it high-stakes or deeply ambiguous?\n      NO → Sonnet ($3/$15)\n        • Most \"hard\" tasks are actually Sonnet-tier\n        \n      YES → Opus ($5/$25)\n        • Architecture planning, complex debugging\n        • Multi-constraint reasoning, prompt engineering\n        • Tasks where quality delta justifies 5x cost\n```\n\n### The Cascade Pattern\nDon't just pick one model — cascade through them:\n\n```python\nfrom anthropic import Anthropic\n\nclient = Anthropic()\n\ndef cascading_call(prompt: str, quality_check) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Try cheapest model first, escalate if quality is insufficient.\"\"\"\n    \n    models = [\n        (\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\", \"haiku\"),\n        (\"claude-sonnet-4-6-20250514\", \"sonnet\"),\n        (\"claude-opus-4-6-20250514\", \"opus\"),\n    ]\n    \n    for model_id, tier in models:\n        response = client.messages.create(\n            model=model_id,\n            max_tokens=1024,\n            messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\n        )\n        \n        result = response.content[0].text\n        \n        if quality_check(result):\n            return {\"text\": result, \"model\": tier, \"tokens\": response.usage}\n    \n    # Opus is the ceiling — return whatever it gave\n    return {\"text\": result, \"model\": \"opus\", \"tokens\": response.usage}\n```\n\n### Router Pattern (Pre-classify, Then Route)\n```python\ndef smart_route(task_type: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Route to cheapest model that meets quality bar.\"\"\"\n    HAIKU = \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\"\n    SONNET = \"claude-sonnet-4-6-20250514\"\n    OPUS = \"claude-opus-4-6-20250514\"\n    \n    routing = {\n        # Mechanical tasks → Haiku\n        \"classify\": HAIKU, \"extract\": HAIKU, \"route\": HAIKU,\n        \"format\": HAIKU, \"tag\": HAIKU, \"validate\": HAIKU,\n        # Creative/analytical → Sonnet\n        \"generate\": SONNET, \"summarize\": SONNET, \"review\": SONNET,\n        \"test\": SONNET, \"analyze\": SONNET, \"explain\": SONNET,\n        # Complex reasoning → Opus\n        \"plan\": OPUS, \"architect\": OPUS, \"debug_complex\": OPUS,\n    }\n    return routing.get(task_type, SONNET)  # Default to Sonnet\n```\n\n---"
