        "heading": "Lever 2: Prompt Caching",
        "content": "Eliminates redundant processing of repeated content.\n\n### How It Works\n```\nRequest 1 (cache WRITE):\n  [System prompt: 5K tokens] ←── cached at 1.25x cost\n  [User message: 200 tokens]  ←── processed normally\n  \nRequest 2-N (cache READ):\n  [System prompt: 5K tokens] ←── served from cache at 0.1x cost (90% off)\n  [User message: 200 tokens]  ←── processed normally\n```\n\n### Key Rules\n- **Prefix-based**: Cache is ordered — tools → system → messages. Anything AFTER a change invalidates.\n- **Minimum tokens**: 4,096 (Opus), 2,048 (Sonnet/Haiku)\n- **TTL**: 5 minutes (default) or 1 hour (explicit). NOT refreshed on hit.\n- **Max 4 breakpoints** per request\n- **Workspace-isolated** since Feb 2026\n\n### Implementation Patterns\n\n#### Auto-Caching (Simplest)\n```python\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6-20250514\",\n    max_tokens=1024,\n    cache_control={\"type\": \"ephemeral\"},  # System handles breakpoint placement\n    system=\"Your large system prompt here...\",\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Question\"}]\n)\n\n# Check cache performance\nprint(f\"Cache written: {response.usage.cache_creation_input_tokens}\")\nprint(f\"Cache read:    {response.usage.cache_read_input_tokens}\")\nprint(f\"Uncached:      {response.usage.input_tokens}\")\n```\n\n#### Explicit Breakpoints (Fine Control)\n```python\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6-20250514\",\n    max_tokens=1024,\n    system=[\n        {\n            \"type\": \"text\",\n            \"text\": \"You are an expert code reviewer...\",  # Stable\n            \"cache_control\": {\"type\": \"ephemeral\"}         # ← Cache this\n        },\n        {\n            \"type\": \"text\",\n            \"text\": full_codebase_contents,                # Stable per session\n            \"cache_control\": {\"type\": \"ephemeral\"}         # ← Cache this too\n        }\n    ],\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Review the auth module\"}]\n)\n```\n\n#### 1-Hour TTL (Lower Frequency Use Cases)\n```python\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6-20250514\",\n    max_tokens=1024,\n    cache_control={\"type\": \"ephemeral\", \"ttl\": \"1h\"},  # 2x write cost, but 1hr window\n    system=\"...\",\n    messages=[...]\n)\n```\n\n### Break-Even Analysis\n```\n5-minute cache:  1.25x write + 0.1x reads → break-even after 1 read\n1-hour cache:    2.0x write + 0.1x reads  → break-even after 2 reads\n\nReal example: 50K token system prompt, Sonnet, 100 requests/hour\n  Without:  100 × 50K × $3/MTok  = $15.00/hr\n  With 5m:  ~12 writes × 50K × $3.75 + 88 reads × 50K × $0.30 = $2.25 + $1.32 = $3.57/hr\n  Savings: 76%\n```\n\n### Performance Bonus\nCache hits reduce Time to First Token (TTFT) by 13-31% — the model skips prefill on cached tokens.\n\n### Critical Gotcha: Ordering Matters\n```python\n# BAD — timestamp changes every request, invalidates everything after it\nsystem=[\n    {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": f\"Time: {datetime.now()}\", \"cache_control\": ...},\n    {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Your stable instructions...\"}  # Never cached!\n]\n\n# GOOD — stable content first, dynamic content last\nsystem=[\n    {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Your stable instructions...\", \"cache_control\": ...},\n    {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": f\"Time: {datetime.now()}\"}  # After breakpoint, not cached\n]\n```\n\n---"
