        "heading": "Lever 3: Batch API",
        "content": "Flat 50% off for anything that can wait up to 24 hours.\n\n### How It Works\n```\nPOST /v1/messages/batches\n  → Submit up to 100,000 requests\n  → Poll for completion (typically < 1 hour, max 24 hours)\n  → Stream results as JSONL\n  → Results available for 29 days\n```\n\n### Implementation\n```python\nfrom anthropic import Anthropic\n\nclient = Anthropic()\n\n# 1. CREATE BATCH\nbatch = client.messages.batches.create(\n    requests=[\n        {\n            \"custom_id\": f\"task-{i}\",\n            \"params\": {\n                \"model\": \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n                \"max_tokens\": 512,\n                \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\n            }\n        }\n        for i, prompt in enumerate(my_prompts)\n    ]\n)\nprint(f\"Batch {batch.id}: {batch.processing_status}\")\n\n# 2. POLL (or use webhooks)\nimport time\nwhile True:\n    status = client.messages.batches.retrieve(batch.id)\n    if status.processing_status == \"ended\":\n        break\n    time.sleep(30)\n\n# 3. COLLECT RESULTS\nfor entry in client.messages.batches.results(batch.id):\n    if entry.result.type == \"succeeded\":\n        print(f\"{entry.custom_id}: {entry.result.message.content[0].text}\")\n    elif entry.result.type == \"errored\":\n        print(f\"{entry.custom_id} FAILED: {entry.result.error.message}\")\n```\n\n### Key Details\n- **Max per batch**: 100,000 requests / 256 MB payload\n- **Results order**: NOT guaranteed — use `custom_id` to match\n- **Partial failures**: Individual requests can fail without killing the batch\n- **Cancellation**: Stops new processing, keeps already-completed results\n- **Cache in batches**: Works but hit rate is best-effort (30-98%)\n\n### When to Batch\n- Nightly data processing, eval suites, bulk classification\n- Content generation pipelines, dataset labeling\n- Anything where the user isn't waiting for a response\n\n---"
